.\" docs/man/meow.1
.TH MEOW 1 "2025-09-19" "meowg1k" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
meow \- your purr-sonal AI sidekick for the terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B meow
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIflags\fR] [\fIarguments...\fR]
.br
For command\-specific flags, run:
.B meow
\fIcommand\fR \-\-help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B meow
is a fast, script\-friendly AI CLI that supports multiple LLM providers
through a configuration\-driven approach. It uses reusable profiles to
simplify working with cloud models (Gemini, OpenAI, OpenRouter) and
local inference (llama.cpp, OpenAI\-compatible APIs).
.br
Input can be provided via flags and/or piped through stdin.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B generate
Generate content using configured profiles. Supports predefined tasks
and custom prompts. Works with all supported providers.
.TP
.B version
Show version info.
.TP
.B completion
Generate shell completion scripts.

.SH OPTIONS
Global options:
.TP
.BR \-c , " \-\-config " \fIFILE\fR
Use specific configuration file. When specified, ignores project and user
configuration files completely.
.TP
.BR \-h , " \-\-help"
Show help for
.B meow
or a specific command.

.SH PROVIDERS
.TP
.B gemini
Google Gemini models. Requires
.B MEOW_GEMINI_API_KEY
environment variable.
.TP
.B openai
OpenAI models (GPT\-4, GPT\-3.5, etc.). Requires
.B MEOW_OPENAI_API_KEY
environment variable.
.TP
.B openrouter
OpenRouter aggregated models. Requires
.B MEOW_OPENROUTER_API_KEY
environment variable.
.TP
.B anthropic
Anthropic Claude models. Requires
.B MEOW_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
environment variable.
.TP
.B voyage
Voyage AI embeddings (recommended by Anthropic). Requires
.B MEOW_VOYAGE_API_KEY
environment variable. Embeddings only.
.TP
.B llama
Local llama.cpp HTTP server. Optionally uses
.B MEOW_LLAMA_API_KEY
environment variable. Requires explicit baseURL in profile.
.TP
.B openai\-compatible
Custom OpenAI\-compatible APIs. Requires
.B MEOW_OPENAI_COMPATIBLE_API_KEY
environment variable and explicit baseURL.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MEOW_GEMINI_API_KEY
API key for the Gemini provider.
.TP
.B MEOW_OPENAI_API_KEY
API key for the OpenAI provider.
.TP
.B MEOW_OPENROUTER_API_KEY
API key for the OpenRouter provider.
.TP
.B MEOW_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
API key for the Anthropic provider.
.TP
.B MEOW_VOYAGE_API_KEY
API key for the Voyage AI provider (embeddings only).
.TP
.B MEOW_LLAMA_API_KEY
Optional API key for the llama provider.
.TP
.B MEOW_OPENAI_COMPATIBLE_API_KEY
API key for OpenAI\-compatible providers.

.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration uses a profile\-based system. Files are read with this precedence:
.IP "1." 3
Explicit config via \fB\-\-config\fR flag (overrides all others)
.IP "2."
Project config:
.B ./.meowg1k/config.yaml
.IP "3."
User config:
.B ~/.config/meowg1k/config.yaml
.PP
Profiles define reusable provider configurations with smart defaults.
See
.BR meow\-config (5)
for detailed configuration syntax.

.SH EXAMPLES
Use a predefined task:
.br
.B cat main.go | meow generate \-t review
.PP
Direct prompt generation:
.br
.B echo "Create a REST API" | meow generate \-p "Write Go code"
.PP
Use specific provider via environment:
.br
.B export MEOW_OPENAI_API_KEY="sk\-..."
.br
.B cat service.py | meow generate \-p "Add error handling"
.PP
Project\-specific configuration:
.br
Create
.B ./.meowg1k/config.yaml
with custom profiles, then:
.br
.B cat auth.go | meow generate \-t security

.SH FILES
.B ~/.config/meowg1k/config.yaml
\- user configuration
.br
.B ./.meowg1k/config.yaml
\- project configuration

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success, non\-zero on error.

